dustin lance black's 8 events at stanford dustin lance black's 8 facebook twitter email print add to calendar the stanford university drama department the stanford lgbt center and stanford law school present a staged reading of dustin lance black's 8 a documentary play taken from the testimony of the federal prop 8 trial perry v brown the performance is part of a nation wide series of readings of the text the us supreme court banned pubic broadcast of the trial and the play brings to the public the impassioned arguments made on both sides of this landmark case please stay for a post show roundtable as artists lawyers and scholars discuss the issues raised in the performance when monday march 5 2012 7 00 pm where please note a change in location cemex auditorium knight management center graduate school of business map audience general public faculty staff students tags arts performance drama public service sponsor stanford law school lgbt community resources center department of drama contact lmantoan stanford edu admission free & open to the public please reserve tickets here permalink http events stanford edu events 306 30655 more info last modified february 29 2012
